F. Recommended Target Design

Minimal Unification Model

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              RuntimeSafetyContext                 │
│  (frozen at startup, required by all gates)      │
│  - profile: ResolvedRuntimeConfig                │
│  - permission: ExecutionPermission               │
│  - config_hash: str                              │
└──────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
               │
    ┌──────────┴──────────────────────────────────┐
    │         ExecutionPermissionGate               │
    │  Single check point for ALL exchange calls    │
    │  Wraps ExchangeGateway.place_order() and      │
    │  cancel_order() with permission verification  │
    └──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
               │
    ┌──────────┴──────────────────────────────────┐
    │         GlobalKillSwitchGate                  │
    │  PG-backed, checked before every new entry    │
    │  GKS deactivation requires multi-factor auth  │
    └──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
               │
    ┌──────────┴──────────────────────────────────┐
    │         CapitalProtectionGate                 │
    │  Extends pre_order_check() to include:        │
    │  - max_leverage enforcement                   │
    │  - max_notional enforcement                   │
    │  Required by ALL entry paths (not just        │
    │  execute_signal)                              │
    └──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
               │
    ┌──────────┴──────────────────────────────────┐
    │         ScriptSafetyBootstrap                 │
    │  All scripts must call bootstrap() before     │
    │  any exchange/DB-runtime-state operation      │
    │  Validates: profile, permission, GKS, env     │
    │  Fails closed if any check missing            │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Key design principles:

1. RuntimeSafetyContext — Created once at startup, frozen, passed to all safety gates. Eliminates multi-track config ambiguity by resolving all values once.
2. ExecutionPermissionGate — Wraps ExchangeGateway at the constructor level. Every place_order() / cancel_order() call passes through it. Scripts cannot bypass by instantiating their own gateway.
3. GlobalKillSwitchGate — GKS deactivation requires: (a) OWNER_APPROVED_GKS_DEACTIVATION env var, (b) PG authorization record, (c) confirmation prompt. Repository rejects set_state(active=False) without authorization.
4. CapitalProtectionGate — Extends pre_order_check() to include max_leverage and max_notional. Required by ExecutionPermissionGate — no way to bypass by injecting a no-op.
5. ScriptSafetyBootstrap — A bootstrap_safety_context() function that scripts call before any operation. Validates environment, profile, permission, GKS state. Returns a RuntimeSafetyContext or raises. Scripts that skip bootstrap cannot obtain a gateway instance.

